Job Description
SharePoint Developer, responsible for the design, development and maintenance SharePoint 2010/13 and online sites. Work on research and development of the latest SharePoint tools and technologies. Use best practices to customize SharePoint sites with custom dashboards, web parts as well as using .NET to extend SharePoint portals and integrate 3rd party applications. This is a unique opportunity for a self-motivated and forward-thinking individual. This individual will report to the Chief Information Technologist and interface with the business divisions on developing premier business solutions based on SharePoint.
Job Specification
Key Areas of Responsibility: Installation of Sharepoint Server on Client MachineDesigning SharePoint solutions, site taxonomy, UX, and record storage Building and implementing custom UI designs for SharePoint with Adobe Photoshop, ASP.NET, HTML, JavaScript, and C# Creating and modifying SharePoint site collections with multiple sites, unique navigational elements, custom content types and site columns, site pages, web part pages, workflows, retention policies, and governance policies Building forms with ASP.NET and Visual Studio Developer for SharePoint application pages Implementing document and record center repositoriesDocumenting solutions with Microsoft Office Performing your job both on-site and off-site (i.e. at customer sites) Superior attention to detail, problem-solving and organizational skills Ability to work effectively with minimal supervision in an atmosphere of multiple projects, shifting priorities, and deadline pressure Other duties as assigned
